<plot>Ravana, king of Lanka, propitiates the god Shiva and, when he wins a boon, claims in return the latter's phallic powers and his consort Parvati. Narada tells Ravana that the Parvati who has been sent is merely a shadow of the goddess. Ravana marries Mandodhiri believing her to be Parvati, but he is condemned by his mother Kaikasi. As for the 'atma-linga', the symbol of Shiva's magical powers, it is donated on condition that it never be set down on earth.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?068363</url></doc>
